<subSubSection id="B2C756855C2E3C6C7BD0FCF1FCA2FB97" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA62050E5C2E3C6A7BD0FCF1FAA7FC0F" blockId="2.[843,1496,798,984]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7BD0FCF1FBF9FCE1" author="HACKEL, E." box="[896,1115,798,822]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" pagination="401 - 419" refId="ref5465" refString="HACKEL, E. (1881). Die verwandtschaftlichen Beziehungen und die geographische Verbreitung der europaischen Festuca-arten. Bot. Centralbl. 4: 401 - 419." type="journal article" year="1881">HACKEL (1881: 405)</bibRefCitation>
published the name 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C2E3C6A7D67FCF1FC29FC81" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ovina" subSpecies="laevis">
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7D67FCF1FA27FCE1" box="[1335,1413,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">F.ovina</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7B1BFCD1FC29FC81" box="[843,907,830,854]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7C61FCD1FABDFC81" author="MCNEILL, J. &amp; ARRIE, H. - M. &amp; BURDET, V. &amp; DEMOULIN, D. L. &amp; HAWKSWORTH, K. &amp; MARHOLD, D. H. &amp; NICOLSON, J. &amp; PRADO, P. C. &amp; SILVA, J. E. &amp; SKOG, J. H." box="[1073,1311,830,854]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" pagination="146" refId="ref5582" refString="MCNEILL, J., F. R. B ARRIE, H. - M. BURDET, V. DEMOULIN, D. L. HAWKSWORTH, K. MARHOLD, D. H. NICOLSON, J. PRADO, P. C. SILVA, J. E. SKOG, J. H. WIERSEMA &amp; N. TURLAND (2006). International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code) adopted by the Seventeenth International Botanical Congress Vienna, Austria, July 2005. Regnum Veg. 146." type="journal article" year="2006">MCNEILL &amp; al. (2006</bibRefCitation>
, art. 32.1, 41.3), this name is not validly published in this paper, because it is accompanied neither by a description, nor by a reference to a previously published description; consequently, even this infraspecific taxon has no taxonomic “status”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA62050E5C2E3C6A7BD0FC07FAA7FB75" blockId="2.[843,1494,1000,1186]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">
Within this invalid “ 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C2E3C6A7C08FC07FB43FBD7" authority="HACKEL (1881: 405)" authorityName="HACKEL" authorityPageNumber="405" authorityYear="1881" box="[1112,1249,1000,1024]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ovina" subSpecies="laevis">
subsp. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7CF3FC07FB43FBD7" box="[1187,1249,1000,1024]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7CAAFC07FA77FBD7" author="HACKEL, E." box="[1274,1493,1000,1024]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" pagination="401 - 419" refId="ref5465" refString="HACKEL, E. (1881). Die verwandtschaftlichen Beziehungen und die geographische Verbreitung der europaischen Festuca-arten. Bot. Centralbl. 4: 401 - 419." type="journal article" year="1881">HACKEL (1881: 405)</bibRefCitation>
reports six different varieties. Among these, a “ 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C2E3C6A7D14FBE7FA13FBF7" box="[1348,1457,1032,1056]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ovina" variety="laevis">
var. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7D23FBE7FA13FBF7" box="[1395,1457,1032,1056]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is described, for which he reports the following distribution: “Gebirge Siciliens, Neapol., nördl. Appenninen, Seealpen, Sierra do Alcoy in SO.- 
<collectingCountry id="82CA459E5C2E3C6A7C1BFB85FB09FB55" box="[1099,1195,1130,1154]" name="Spain" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">Spanien</collectingCountry>
; Daya in 
<collectingCountry id="82CA459E5C2E3C6A7D43FB85FAFCFB55" box="[1299,1374,1130,1154]" name="Algeria" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">Algier</collectingCountry>
; Kreta.” A reference to “Guss. Fl. sic.” is also given.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA62050E5C2E3C6A7BD0FB5DFADDFA39" blockId="2.[843,1497,1202,1518]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">
Actually, even the name 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C2E3C6A7CCDFB5DFAD6FB1D" box="[1181,1396,1202,1226]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ovina" variety="laevis">
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7CCDFB5DFB52FB1D" box="[1181,1264,1202,1226]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">F.ovina</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7D63FB5DFAD6FB1D" box="[1331,1396,1202,1226]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be regarded as not validly published, as it lacks either a description or a reference to a previously published description (
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7B03FAFCFB9AFAFC" author="MCNEILL, J. &amp; ARRIE, H. - M. &amp; BURDET, V. &amp; DEMOULIN, D. L. &amp; HAWKSWORTH, K. &amp; MARHOLD, D. H. &amp; NICOLSON, J. &amp; PRADO, P. C. &amp; SILVA, J. E. &amp; SKOG, J. H." box="[851,1080,1299,1323]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" pagination="146" refId="ref5582" refString="MCNEILL, J., F. R. B ARRIE, H. - M. BURDET, V. DEMOULIN, D. L. HAWKSWORTH, K. MARHOLD, D. H. NICOLSON, J. PRADO, P. C. SILVA, J. E. SKOG, J. H. WIERSEMA &amp; N. TURLAND (2006). International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code) adopted by the Seventeenth International Botanical Congress Vienna, Austria, July 2005. Regnum Veg. 146." type="journal article" year="2006">MCNEILL &amp; al., 2006</bibRefCitation>
, art. 32.1, 41.3). As a matter of fact, no description is reported, and even the reference to “Guss. Fl. sic.” is not “a clear indication” (M CNEILL &amp; al., 2006, art. 32.6), as it is not clear whether Hackel refers to G USSONE (1827: 102) or to 
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7C53FA7AFB77FA7A" author="GUSSONE, G." box="[1027,1237,1429,1453]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" refId="ref5429" refString="GUSSONE, G. (1843). Florae siculae synopsis. Vol. 1. Napoli." type="book" year="1843">GUSSONE (1843: 86)</bibRefCitation>
, and it must be reminded that in the two publications two different descriptions and systematic circumscriptions for the species are reported.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA62050E5C2E3C6A7BD0FA11FA26F96F" blockId="2.[843,1494,1534,1720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">
According to the above considerations, the name 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C2E3C6A7DD2FA11FC6FF9E0" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ovina" subSpecies="laevi">
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7DD2FA11FA6DF9C1" box="[1410,1487,1534,1558]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">F.ovina</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7BC8F9F0FC6FF9E0" box="[920,973,1567,1591]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">laevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s was validly published only in H ACKEL (1882), where the name of this taxon is accompanied by a short diagnosis in the identification key (
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7CC1F9B0FAEDF9A0" author="HACKEL, E." box="[1169,1359,1631,1655]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL 1882: 84</bibRefCitation>
), by a whole description (
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7B80F96FFB03F94F" author="HACKEL, E." box="[976,1185,1664,1688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL, 1882: 107</bibRefCitation>
) and by a figure showing the section of a leaf blade (
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7C14F94FFB7EF96F" author="HACKEL, E." box="[1092,1244,1696,1720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL 1882</bibRefCitation>
: tab. III, fig. 7).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA62050E5C2E3C6A7BD0F927FA80F874" blockId="2.[843,1494,1736,1955]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">
Within this subspecies, H ACKEL (1882: 108-112) describes five varieties and among these a “ 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C2E3C6A7D69F906FA6BF8D6" authority="HACKEL (1882: 108-110)" authorityName="HACKEL" authorityPageNumber="108 - 110" authorityYear="1882" baseAuthorityName="HACKEL" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[1337,1481,1769,1793]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ovina" variety="genuina">
var. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7D20F906FA6BF8D6" box="[1392,1481,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">genuina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7B1BF8E6FBFAF8F6" author="HACKEL, E." box="[843,1112,1801,1825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL (1882: 108-110)</bibRefCitation>
. This last includes five subvarieties, and among these a “subvar. α 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7CC3F8C5FB77F895" box="[1171,1237,1834,1858]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">typica</emphasis>
” (
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7CA0F8C5FA6BF895" author="HACKEL, E." box="[1264,1481,1834,1858]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL, 1882: 109</bibRefCitation>
). Neither 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C2E3C6A7BF4F8A5FB25F8B5" baseAuthorityName="HACKEL" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[932,1159,1866,1890]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ovina" variety="genuina">
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7BF4F8A5FC56F8B5" box="[932,1012,1866,1890]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">F.ovina</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7C60F8A5FB25F8B5" box="[1072,1159,1866,1890]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">genuina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nor 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C2E3C6A7CEAF8A5FA0CF8B5" box="[1210,1454,1866,1890]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subVariety" species="ovina" subVariety="typica">
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7CEAF8A5FAA8F8B5" box="[1210,1290,1866,1890]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">F.ovina</emphasis>
subvar. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2E3C6A7D3CF8A5FA0CF8B5" box="[1388,1454,1866,1890]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">typica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are validly published here, as both infraspecific epithets are not allowed by 
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C2E3C6A7B98F864FB08F874" author="MCNEILL, J. &amp; ARRIE, H. - M. &amp; BURDET, V. &amp; DEMOULIN, D. L. &amp; HAWKSWORTH, K. &amp; MARHOLD, D. H. &amp; NICOLSON, J. &amp; PRADO, P. C. &amp; SILVA, J. E. &amp; SKOG, J. H." box="[968,1194,1931,1955]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" pagination="146" refId="ref5582" refString="MCNEILL, J., F. R. B ARRIE, H. - M. BURDET, V. DEMOULIN, D. L. HAWKSWORTH, K. MARHOLD, D. H. NICOLSON, J. PRADO, P. C. SILVA, J. E. SKOG, J. H. WIERSEMA &amp; N. TURLAND (2006). International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code) adopted by the Seventeenth International Botanical Congress Vienna, Austria, July 2005. Regnum Veg. 146." type="journal article" year="2006">MCNEILL &amp; al., 2006</bibRefCitation>
(art. 24.3).
</paragraph>
<caption id="AEA255865C2F3C6B7837F885FD52F848" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5718960" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5718960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5718960/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" startId="3.[103,128,1898,1918]" targetBox="[102,1479,279,1876]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="FA62050E5C2F3C6B7837F885FD52F848" blockId="3.[103,752,1898,1951]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C2F3C6B7837F885FF06F8A9" bold="true" box="[103,164,1898,1918]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Fig. 1. –</emphasis>
Lectotypus of 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C2F3C6B7942F885FDB9F8A9" authority="Hack." authorityName="Hack." box="[274,539,1898,1918]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ovina" subSpecies="laevis">Festuca ovina subsp. laevis Hack.</taxonomicName>
[Todaro s.n., W] [© Naturhistorisches Museum 
<collectingRegion id="3819CBEC5C2F3C6B7988F864FDA4F848" box="[472,518,1931,1951]" country="Austria" name="Wien" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Wien</collectingRegion>
. Reproduced with permission]
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="FA62050E5C283C6C78FBFEF6FCA1FE65" blockId="4.[118,771,281,1089]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">
Yet, the name 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C283C6C7914FEF6FDAEFEE6" box="[324,524,281,305]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ovina" variety="laevis">
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C283C6C7914FEF6FE31FEE6" box="[324,403,281,305]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">F.ovina</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C283C6C799EFEF6FDAEFEE6" box="[462,524,281,305]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is validly published in 
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C283C6C7826FED6FEE0FE86" author="HACKEL, E." box="[118,322,313,337]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL (1882: 84)</bibRefCitation>
in the identification key, where the epithet is correct and the name is accompanied by a short diagnosis. Moreover, in the index (
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C283C6C793DFE95FD90FE45" author="HACKEL, E." box="[365,562,378,402]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL 1882: 213</bibRefCitation>
) the name “ 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C283C6C7AFFFE95FF43FE65" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ovina" subSpecies="laevis">F. ovina ssp. laevis</taxonomicName>
m. 107” is reported, followed by “ 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C283C6C7A1CFE75FD00FE65" box="[588,674,410,434]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ovina" variety="laevis">v. laevis</taxonomicName>
m. 108”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA62050E5C283C6C78FBFE50FD61FCCE" blockId="4.[118,771,281,1089]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">
This also means that 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C283C6C79D8FE50FE53FE00" box="[392,497,447,471]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ovina" variety="laevis">
var. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C283C6C79E4FE50FE53FE00" box="[436,497,447,471]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of both the key (
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C283C6C7AF3FE50FF7AFE20" author="HACKEL, E." pageId="4" pageNumber="225" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL, 1882: 84</bibRefCitation>
) and the index (
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C283C6C79D6FE30FDFFFE20" author="HACKEL, E." box="[390,605,479,503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL, 1882: 213</bibRefCitation>
) exactly corresponds to the 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C283C6C7944FE10FE3DFDC0" baseAuthorityName="HACKEL" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[276,415,511,535]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ovina" variety="genuina">
var. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C283C6C7916FE10FE3DFDC0" box="[326,415,511,535]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">genuina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
invalidly described in H ACKEL (1882: 108). Consequently, even the full description and all the other features reported in the monograph for this 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C283C6C7A87FDAFFE4BFDAF" authority="(HACKEL, 1882: 108 - 110)" baseAuthorityName="HACKEL" baseAuthorityPageNumber="108 - 110" baseAuthorityYear="1882" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ovina" variety="genuina">
var. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C283C6C7826FD8FFF6FFDAF" box="[118,205,608,632]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">genuina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C283C6C788BFD8FFE40FDAF" author="HACKEL, E." box="[219,482,608,632]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL, 1882: 108-110</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
are to be attributed to the validly published 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C283C6C7960FD6FFE52FD4F" box="[304,496,640,664]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="223" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ovina" variety="laevis">
F. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C283C6C7918FD6FFE20FD4F" box="[328,386,640,664]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">ovina</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C283C6C79E3FD6FFE52FD4F" box="[435,496,640,664]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C283C6C79AEFD6FFD1DFD4F" author="HACKEL, E." box="[510,703,640,664]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL, 1882: 84</bibRefCitation>
, 107), including the following synonyms: “ 
<taxonomicName id="3DDD7E8D5C283C6C79A5FD4EFF31FD0E" authority="Guss. Prodr. Fl." authorityName="Guss. Prodr. Fl." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="duriuscula">F. duriuscula Guss. Prodr. Fl.</taxonomicName>
sic. 102 (1827). – Synops. 86 (1842). Parl. Fl. palerm. 198 (1845) non L.” (
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C283C6C794DFD0EFE4BFD2E" author="HACKEL, E." box="[285,489,737,761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL, 1882: 109</bibRefCitation>
), and this distribution area: “ 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C283C6C78D2FCEEFE76FCCE" box="[130,468,769,793]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">In montibus Europae australis”</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C283C6C79B3FCEEFD17FCCE" author="HACKEL, E." box="[483,693,769,793]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL, 1882: 110</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA62050E5C283C6C78FBFCC9FCA2FB97" blockId="4.[118,771,281,1089]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">
To be legitimate, these two infraspecific names are necessarily homotypic (
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C283C6C791EFCA8FD97FC88" author="MCNEILL, J. &amp; ARRIE, H. - M. &amp; BURDET, V. &amp; DEMOULIN, D. L. &amp; HAWKSWORTH, K. &amp; MARHOLD, D. H. &amp; NICOLSON, J. &amp; PRADO, P. C. &amp; SILVA, J. E. &amp; SKOG, J. H." box="[334,565,839,863]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" pagination="146" refId="ref5582" refString="MCNEILL, J., F. R. B ARRIE, H. - M. BURDET, V. DEMOULIN, D. L. HAWKSWORTH, K. MARHOLD, D. H. NICOLSON, J. PRADO, P. C. SILVA, J. E. SKOG, J. H. WIERSEMA &amp; N. TURLAND (2006). International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code) adopted by the Seventeenth International Botanical Congress Vienna, Austria, July 2005. Regnum Veg. 146." type="journal article" year="2006">MCNEILL &amp; al., 2006</bibRefCitation>
, art 53.4). The 
<typeStatus id="2566BBAC5C283C6C7A88FCA8FF14FCA8" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">lectotype</typeStatus>
here designated was chosen within the specimens hosted in W, where Hackel’s personal herbarium is kept; the label bears some notes handwritten by Hackel and all the morphological characters perfectly fit the original description. It appears to be a duplicate of the specimen 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C283C6C7A7FFC07FF7FFBF7" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">“TodaroFl.sic. exs nro. 444”</emphasis>
collected by 
<collectorName id="572860D85C283C6C7938FBE7FE13FBF7" box="[360,433,1032,1056]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">Todaro</collectorName>
in 
<collectingRegion id="3819CBEC5C283C6C7982FBE7FDADFBF7" box="[466,527,1032,1056]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">Sicily</collectingRegion>
and cited by Hackel in the protologue (sub “subvar. α 
<emphasis id="C8A9D91C5C283C6C7993FBC7FDA6FB97" box="[451,516,1064,1088]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">typica</emphasis>
”; 
<bibRefCitation id="9E4C78FF5C283C6C7A4EFBC7FD56FB97" author="HACKEL, E." box="[542,756,1064,1088]" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" refId="ref5494" refString="HACKEL, E. (1882). MonographiaFestucarum Europearum. Berlin." type="book" year="1882">HACKEL, 1882: 109</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
